3 The purpose of this Act is to ensure the health, safety,
4 and welfare of the citizens of the State by requiring the
5 counties to:
6 (1) Regulate the permitting, construction, and maintenance
7 of retention and detention ponds, including
8 establishing safety standards for retention and
9 detention ponds; and
10 (2) Conduct a survey of existing retention and detention
11 ponds Statewide and submit a report to the
12 legislature.
13 This Act also recognizes Charlotte "Sharkey" Schaefers, the
14 five-year-old girl who drowned at a Pearl City naval housing
15 complex while trying to save the life of her childhood friend.
16 SECTION 2. Chapter 46, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is amended
17 by adding a new section to be appropriately designated and to
18 read as follows:
19 "§46- Retention ponds and detention ponds; safety
20 requirements. (a) This section shall be known and may be cited
21 as "Sharkey's Law".
