10 (d) For the purposes of this section:
11 "Detention pond" means an area that is designed to:
12 (1) Hold stormwater until the effects of percolation,
13 evapotranspiration, or controlled release return the
14 area to its normally dry state; and
15 (2) Dissipate inflowing stormwater within seventy-two
16 hours to accommodate a new volume of water.
17 "Retention pond" means a permanent or semi-permanent
18 aquatic system that acts as a trap where pollutants picked up by
19 the initial surge of stormwater settle out before leaving the
20 system."
